<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-08-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-08-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="714" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d714">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Baron <persName type="from">Ketteler</persName> to
                                Mr. <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">New
                                        York</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-08-17"><hi rend="italic">August 17,
                                1893</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>In reply to your inquiry, I am instructed to state that the Imperial
                            Government, in view of the peaceful situation at Apia, do not consider
                            the dispatch of U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Philadelphia</hi> to Samoa to
                            be of any further necessity. An official answer to your note will be
                            forwarded to-day.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Ketteler.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>